**TLDR' on `approve2` plugin:**
This plugin is an updated approve plugin that supports
granular approvals and regex in the OWNERS files

This commit adds a new PR status section to the approval notifier message.
This section shows the status of approvals of the folders involved in the PR.
It shows if all the files under a folder are completely approved, partially approved
or unapproved. The folders used are the ones where the owners files associated
with the original PR reside.

Activities.Body: Capture konnectivity logs to help debug flaky scalability test where konnecivity-agent is sometimes restarted.

Should it be "containers/konnectivity-*" to match https://github.com/kubernetes/test-infra/commit/8fbc6048fb3d844f8c013fb34695e307fc7124ef?

Also: https://github.com/kubernetes/test-infra/commit/8fbc6048fb3d844f8c013fb34695e307fc7124ef fetches this log only on nodes (for all cloud providers) with log-dump.sh and this change fetches only for gce and both on nodes and masters.

Is the discrepancy between log-dump.sh and logexporter intended? They both try to do the same thing so I would expect them to implement similar logic.

Working on making it better match containers. log-dump and logexporter differences were part of dims response and working on that as well. The konnectivity system is only enabled on GCE (that I know of). I intended this to be on both nodes and masters. On nodes it grabs the agent logs and on masters it should grab the server log.

Activities.Body:
The following two test suites are failing in `gce-cos-k8sstable2-alphafeatures` on the sig-release-1.19-blocking dashboard for a long time:

* `[sig-network] Networking Granular Checks: Services should function for pod-Service: sctp [Feature:SCTPConnectivity]`
* `[sig-network] Networking should function for pod-pod: sctp [Feature:SCTPConnectivity]`

I've investigated a bit and found that we disabled those tests for other `alphafeatures` jobs. From #17125:

> The tests tagged as [Feature:SCTPConnectivity]" were not supposed to run on Kubernetes CI, however, the regex in the job ci-kubernetes-e2e-gci-gce-alpha-features wasn't excluding it and started to run them, with the problem that they started to fail :)

/assign @justaugustus 
cc: @kubernetes/release-engineering
I'm not sure if this is actually correct. Can someone confirm or point me in the right direction if it's wrong?

the `Networking-Performance and IPv6` have the `Feature:` as well? why was not like this before?

myabe we keep: `--ginkgo.skip=Networking-Performance|IPv6|Feature:(Volumes| SCTPConnectivity)` ? not sure as well
@cpanato This makes sense to me. I modified the PR to do what you proposed, PTAL again.

/lgtm
thanks!

Activities.Body:
The flag `--restart-kubelet` was added to the test suite in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/97028

However as it turns out, in order to test the exit on lock contention, it is not needed, hence removing the flag from the test job.

The corresponding PR for the e2e test is https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/103608.

Locally the test can be tested without requiring the `--restart-kubelet` flag
```
make test-e2e-node REMOTE=false TEST_ARGS="--kubelet-flags=\"--lock-file=/var/run/kubelet.lock --exit-on-lock-contention --v 4\"" FOCUS="\[NodeFeature:LockContention\]" SKIP="\[Flaky\]|\[Serial\]"
```


/cc @knabben @rata
why do we need this new skip flag? it will not do much, will it?

@SergeyKanzhelev Locally If I don't add a `skip`, the test is getting skipped. I think because the default value of skip is to skip slow disruptive tests which this test is.

Locally I then had to add `SKIP=""`. I looked at other tests in the file and picked this option,
oh, I see. You just override the default. In this case you might try to override it to empty.

```suggestion
          - --test_args=--nodes=1 --focus="\[NodeFeature:LockContention\]" --skip=""
```

like this ?

@SergeyKanzhelev
yes, this expresses the intent better I think. As long as it works
done.
/lgtm
/lgtm

CodeChangeRequest.Title: Remove restart kubelet flag from e2e lock contention
